          "title": "We’re There. What Comes After?",
          "guidingSection": "Concluding Questions",
          "rawOfficialText": "This ending is clear: we’re there. Where do we go next?",
          "links": [],
          "studentExplanation": "The theme ends by finally saying the words students have been waiting for: we’re there. But the next sentence immediately opens a new journey. That is the point: arrival can be real, but it rarely ends thinking, growth, or movement. A finished route can become a beginning, and a destination can become the place where the next question starts.\n\nTreat this as the final pivot of the whole theme: arrival is real, but it is not the same as disappearance of motion. A finish line can become a starting line, a graduation can become a new uncertainty, and the phrase “we’re there” matters because it immediately raises the next destination. Use this to return to the theme: what counts as arrival, when waiting or quitting becomes reasonable, how closure changes a story or decision, and why getting there often opens another question.",
          "whyItMatters": "At the entry level, this closes the theme with a simple but powerful reversal. At the section level, it turns concluding questions into a doorway toward what comes next. At the year-theme level, it connects to journeys and endings because the final answer to “Are we there yet?” is not just yes; it is also “what now?”",
          "takeaway": "Getting there often begins the next journey",
