          "guidingSection": "We're All in This to Get There",
          "rawOfficialText": "As returning scholars might remember, some big projects take much too long to finish - high speed rail in California, the Haunted Chocolatier, these outlines. Some never get there at all. Explore the following examples of projects that were not finished on time, then discuss with your team: What factors, if any, did these delays have in common? How would you have overcome them? And are there projects out there in the world today that you predict will suffer a similar fate?\n\nLa Sagrada Familia | Spain\nNusantara Capital City | Indonesia\nRyugyong Hotel | North Korea\nWonderland Amusement Park | China\nBerlin Brandenburg Airport | Germany\nMilan Cathedral | Italy\nCrazy Horse Memorial | South Dakota",
